    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-12-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-01-11T15:53:30Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Emergency Relief Tax Check-Off for Our Armed Forces Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax deduction (available to taxpayers who do not itemize their tax deductions) for charitable contributions of up to $1,000 ($2,000 in the case of a joint return) to the Armed Forces Relief Trust. </p><p>Allows taxpayers to designate on their tax returns a portion of any overpayment of tax as a contribution to the Trust or to make a cash contribution to the Trust with their tax returns.</p><p>Establishes an advisory board to advise the Trust on its operation and on the distribution of contributed funds. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
